l's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":0,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":9,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":54,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Alice Arundel was born in 1328, in Arundel Castle, Sussex, England. She married Sir John Brachton I in 1353. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter."},"et":{"1328–":"1328–Surnud","1324–1410":"1324–1410","1354–1410":"1354–1410","1359–1410":"1359–1410","1328–Female":"1328–Surnud","1359":"1359","1337":"1337","1324":"1324","1410":"1410","1354":"1354","1453":"1453","1353":"1353","1382":"1382","1328":"1328","Arundel Castle, Sussex, kingdom of england":"Arundel Castle, Sussex, England","Norfolk, kingdom of England":"Norfolk, England","Norfolk, Eng